msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/spring-projects-in.adoc:290
msgid ""
"Dealing with generic types in Spring applications written in Kotlin may "
"require, for some use cases, to understand Kotlin "
"{kotlin-docs}/generics.html#declaration-site-variance[declaration-site "
"variance] which allows to define the variance when declaring a type, which "
"is not possible in Java which supports only use-site variance."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/spring-projects-in.adoc:294
msgid ""
"For example, declaring `List<Foo>` in Kotlin is conceptually equivalent to "
"`java.util.List<? extends Foo>` because `kotlin.collections.List` is "
"declared as {kotlin-api}/jvm/stdlib/kotlin.collections/-list/[`interface "
"List<out E> : kotlin.collections.Collection<E>`]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/spring-projects-in.adoc:297
msgid ""
"This needs to be taken into account by using the `out` Kotlin keyword on "
"generic types when using Java classes, for example when writing a "
"`org.springframework.core.convert.converter.Converter` from a Kotlin type to "
"a Java type."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/spring-projects-in.adoc:303
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclass ListOfFooConverter : Converter<List<Foo>, CustomJavaList<out Foo>> "
"{\n"
"\t\t// ...\n"
"\t}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/spring-projects-in.adoc:306
msgid ""
"When converting any kind of objects, star projection with `*` can be used "
"instead of `out Any`."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/spring-projects-in.adoc:311
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclass ListOfAnyConverter : Converter<List<*>, CustomJavaList<*>> {\n"
"\t\t// ...\n"
"\t}\n"
msgstr ""

